obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (43692)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00018_195910_1517807321802&sectionId=43692&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00018_195910_1517807321802
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `This Act may be called the Parliament (Prevention of Disqualification)`
  line `Act, 1959`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (43693)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 54 of 1993, s. 2, for the words "the Salaries and Allowances of Members of Parliament Act, 1954" (w.e.f. 27-8-1993).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00018_195910_1517807321802&sectionId=43693&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00018_195910_1517807321802
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,―`
  line
  line `(a) "compensatory allowance" means any sum of money payable to the holder of an office by`
  line `way of daily allowance (such allowance not exceeding the amount of daily allowance to which a`
  line `member of Parliament is entitled under`
  line `^1[the Salary, Allowances and Pension of Members of`
  line `Parliament Act, 1954 (30 of 1954)], any conveyance allowance, house-rent allowance or`
  line `travelling allowance for the purpose of enabling him to recoup any expenditure incurred by him in`
  line `performing the functions of that office;`
  line
  line `(b) "statutory body" means any corporation, committee, commission, council, board or other`
  line `body of persons, whether incorporated or not, established by or under any law for the time being`
  line `in force;`
  line
  line `(c) "non-statutory body" means any body of persons other than a statutory body.`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (43694)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Certain offices of profit not to disqualify.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00018_195910_1517807321802&sectionId=43694&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00018_195910_1517807321802
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `It is hereby declared that none of the following`
  line `offices, in so far as it is an office of profit under the Government of India or the Government of any`
  line `State, shall disqualify the holder thereof for being chosen as, or for being, a member of Parliament,`
  line namely,--
  line
  line `(a) any office held by a Minister, Minister of State or Deputy Minister for the Union or for`
  line `any State, whether ex officio or by name;`
  line
  line `^1[(aa) the office of a Leader of the Opposition in Parliament;]br`
  line
  line `^2[(ab) the office of Deputy Chairman, Planning Commission;]`
  line
  line `^3[(ac) the office of ^4[each leader and each deputy leader] of a recognised party and a`
  line `recognised group in either House of Parliament;]`
  line
  line `^5[(ad) the office of the Chairperson of the National Advisory Council constituted by the`
  line `Government of India in the Cabinet Secretariat vide Order No. 631/2/1/2004-Cab., dated the 31st`
  line `May, 2004;]`
  line
  line `(b) the office of Chief Whip, Deputy Chief Whip or Whip in Parliament or of a Parliamentary`
  line Secretary;
  line
  line `^6[(ba) the office of chairperson of`
  line
  line `(i) the National Commission for Minorities constituted under section 3 of the National`
  line `Commission for Minorities Act, 1992 (19 of 1992);`
  line
  line `^7[(ii) the National Commission for the Scheduled Castes constituted under clause (1) of`
  line `article 338 of the Constitution;`
  line
  line `(iia) the National Commission for the Scheduled Tribes constituted under clause (1) of`
  line `article 338A of the Constitution;]`
  line
  line `(iii) the National Commission for women constituted under section 3 of the National`
  line `Commission for Women Act, 1990 (20 of 1990);]`
  line
  line `(c) the office of a member of any force raised or maintained under the National Cadet Corps`
  line `Act, 1948 (31 of 1948), the Territorial Army Act, 1948 (56 of 1948), or the Reserve and Auxiliary`
  line `Air Forces Act, 1952 (62 of 1952);`
  line
  line `(d) the office of a member of a Home Guard constituted under any law for the time being in`
  line `force in any State;`
  line
  line `(e) the office of sheriff in the city of Bombay, Calcutta or Madras;`
  line
  line `(f) the office of chairman or member of the syndicate, senate, executive committee, council or`
  line `court of a university or any other body connected with a university;`
  line
  line `(g) the office of a member of any delegation or mission sent outside India by the Government`
  line `for any special purpose;`
  line
  line `(h) the office of chairman or member of a committee (whether consisting of one or more`
  line `members), set up temporarily for the purpose of advising the Government or any other authority`
  line `in respect of any matter of public importance or for the purpose of making an inquiry into, or`
  line `collecting statistics in respect of, any such matter, if the holder of such office is not entitled to any`
  line `remuneration other than compensatory allowance;`
  line
  line `^8[(i)the office of chairman, director or member of any statutory or non-statutory body other than any such body as is referred to in clause (h), if the holder of such office is not entitled to any`
  line `remuneration other than compensatory allowance, but excluding (i) the office of chairman of any`
  line `statutory or non-statutory body specified in Part I of the Schedule, and (ii) the office of chairman`
  line `or secretary of any statutory or non-statutory body specified in Part II of the Schedule;]`
  line
  line `(j) the office of village revenue officer, whether called a lambardar, malguzar, patel`
  line `deshmukh or by any other name, whose duty is to collect land revenue and who is remunerated by`
  line `a share of, or commission on, the amount of land revenue collected by him, but who does not`
  line `discharge any police functions.`
  line
  line `^9[(k) the office of Chairman, Deputy Chairman, Secretary or Member (by whatever name`
  line `called) in any statutory or non-statutory body specified in the Table;`
  line
  line `(l) the office of Chairperson or trustee (by whatever name called) of any Trust, whether public`
  line `or private, not being a body specified in the Schedule;`
  line
  line `(m) the office of Chairman, President, Vice-President or Principal Secretary or`
  line `Secretary of the Governing Body of any society registered under the Societies Registration`
  line `Act, 1860 (21 of 1860) or under any other law relating to registration of societies, not being a`
  line `body specified in the Schedule.]`
  line
  line `^10[Explanation 1.For the purposes of this section, the office of ^11[chairman, Deputy Chairman or`
  line `secretary] shall include every office of that description by whatever name called.`
  line
  line `^12[Explanation 2.--In clause (aa), the expression Leader of the Opposition shall have the`
  line `meaning assigned to it in the Salary and Allowances of Leaders of Opposition in Parliament`
  line `Act, 1977 (33 of 1977).]]`
  line
  line `^13[Explanation 3.--In clause (ac), the expressions recognised party and recognised group shall`
  line `have the meanings assigned to them in the Leaders and Chief Whips of Recognised Parties and`
  line `Groups in Parliament (Facilities) Act, 1998 (5 of 1999).]`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 33 of 1977, s. 12 (w.e.f. 1-11-1977).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 54 of 1993, s. 3 (w.e.f. 19-7-1993).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 5 of 1999, s. 5 (w.e.f. 5-2-1999).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 18 of 2000, s. 5, for each leader (w.e.f. 7-6-2000).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 31 of 2006, s. 2 (w.e.f. 18-8-2006).`
  line `6. Ins. by Act 54 of 1993, s. 3 (w.e.f. 27-8-1993).`
  line `7. Subs. by Act 28 of 2013, s. 2, for sub-clause (ii) (w.e.f. 20-9-2013).`
  line `8. Subs. by Act 54 of 1993, s. 3, for clause (i) (w.e.f. 19-7-1993).`
  line `9. Ins. by Act 31 of 2006, s. 2 (w.e.f. 18-8-2006).`
  line `10. Explanation re-numbered as Explanation 1 thereof by Act 33 of 1977, s. 12 (w.e.f.1-11-1977).`
  line `11. Subs. by Act 54 of 1993, s. 3, for chairman or secretary (w.e.f. 27-8-1993).`
  line `12. Explanation 2 ins. by Act 31 of 1977, s. 12 (w.e.f. 1-11-1977).`
  line `13. Explanation 3 ins. by Act 5 of 1999, s. 5 (w.e.f. 7-1-1999).`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (43695)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Temporary suspension of disqualification in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00018_195910_1517807321802&sectionId=43695&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00018_195910_1517807321802
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `If a person being a member of`
  line `Parliament who immediately before the commencement of this Act held an office of profit declared`
  line `by any law repealed by this Act not to disqualify the holder thereof for being such member, becomes`
  line `so disqualified by reason of any of the provisions contained in this Act, such office shall not, if held`
  line `by such person for any period not extending beyond a period of six months from the commencement`
  line `of this Act disqualify him for being a member of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (43696)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title Repeals.
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00018_195910_1517807321802&sectionId=43696&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00018_195910_1517807321802
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `The Parliament (Prevention of Disqualification) Act, 1950 (19 of 1950), the`
  line `Parliament Prevention of Disqualification Act, 1951 (68 of 1951), the Prevention of Disqualification`
  line `Act, 1953 (1 of 1954), and any provision in any other enactment which is inconsistent with this Act`
  line `are hereby repealed.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
